excerpt: Prominent palace from 1744 with tours & a museum featuring sculptures, weapons & other artifacts.
detail_description: Keraton Surakarta Hadiningrat, established in 1744, stands as a magnificent testament to Javanese history and culture. Once the heart of the Islamic Mataram Kingdom, this royal palace offers visitors an immersive journey through time. The complex features various sections like Alun Alun Lor and Sasana Sumewa, where you can explore museums filled with captivating artifacts such as sculptures and traditional costumes.
name: Keraton Surakarta Hadiningrat
address: Jl. Kamandungan, Baluwarti, Pasar Kliwon, Surakarta City, Central Java 57144, Indonesia

excerpt: Many vendors sell a variety of antiques at this bi-level indoor market open daily & Saturday night.
detail_description: Triwindu Antique Market is a treasure trove for those who appreciate the charm of vintage finds. This enchanting bi-level indoor market, open daily and even on Saturday nights, invites you to explore its maze-like layout across two stories filled with an eclectic mix of antiques. From stunning wrought-iron chandeliers and whimsical leather puppets to nostalgic phonographs and exquisite Dutch porcelain, there's something for everyone here.
name: Triwindu Antique Market
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto, Keprabon, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57131, Indonesia

excerpt: Busy market renowned for its street food, with stalls selling fruit, vegetables & fish.
detail_description: Pasar Gede Hardjonagoro Solo, located in Surakarta, Indonesia, is a bustling market known for its vibrant atmosphere and diverse offerings. Originally built by the Netherlands government and reconstructed in 2016, it stands as one of the largest markets in Solo.
name: Gede Hardjonagoro Market
address: Jl. Jend. Urip Sumoharjo, Sudiroprajan, Jebres, Surakarta City, Central Java 57129, Indonesia

excerpt: Cozy 19th-century history museum showcasing weapons, textiles, manuscripts, sculpture & currency.
detail_description: Museum Radya Pustaka is a charming 19th-century history museum that houses an impressive collection of historic artifacts and scrolls, showcasing weapons, textiles, manuscripts, sculpture, and currency. It is renowned for its heritage from the Mataram Kingdom and features notable items such as porcelain gifted by Napoleon Bonaparte to Paku Buwono IV, king of Surakarta kingdom.
name: Museum Radya Pustaka
address: Slamet Riyadi St No.275, Sriwedari, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57141, Indonesia

detail_description: Pasar Triwindu, situated in the heart of the city, is a treasure trove for antique enthusiasts. It offers a wide array of items such as Javanese daggers, leather puppets, and various decorations. However, shoppers should exercise caution as there are counterfeit products similar to those found at Jalan Surabaya in Jakarta.
name: Pasar Triwindu
address: Keprabon, Kec. Banjarsari, Kota Surakarta, Jawa Tengah, Indonesia

excerpt: International batik museum with vintage fabrics, live-action demonstrations & textiles for sale.
detail_description: House of Danar Hadi is a renowned international batik museum that offers live-action demonstrations, vintage fabrics, and textiles for sale. The museum showcases 1078 handpicked pieces from a collection of 11,000 in a grand colonial building. Visitors can enjoy guided tours tailored to their interests, including demonstrations of the craft and access to a shop. Additionally, the museum provides an interactive experience with modern batik designs where visitors can create their own masterpieces.
name: House of Danar Hadi
address: Slamet Riyadi St No.261, Sriwedari, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57141, Indonesia

excerpt: Mosque built in the 1700s in classic Javanese style, with wood beams & pillars in the prayer hall.
detail_description: Masjid Agung Keraton Surakarta, a stunning example of classic Javanese architecture, was established in 1768 by Sunan Pakubuwono III. Nestled on Kauman Street in Central Java, this royal mosque serves as both a Friday prayer venue and a site for significant royal traditions. Its striking tajuk roof and intricate designs reflect the rich cultural heritage of the region.
name: Masjid Agung Keraton Surakarta
address: Jl. Masjid Agung No.1, Kauman, Pasar Kliwon, Surakarta City, Central Java 57122, Indonesia

excerpt: Low-key amusement park offering children's rides & cultural entertainment such as puppet shows.
detail_description: Sriwedari Park is an amusement park with a historical significance that has been around for centuries. It offers children's rides and cultural entertainment such as puppet shows that showcase Solo's traditional culture of batik. The annual Solo Batik Carnival is held here, featuring avant-garde displays of the local tradition. Additionally, there are weekly traditional puppet shows to enjoy in the comfortable indoor venue with AC and no smoking allowed.
name: Sriwedari Park
address: Slamet Riyadi St No.275, Sriwedari, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57141, Indonesia

excerpt: Lively weekend nighttime marketplace with many vendors offering handicrafts, food & live music.
name: Ngarsopuro Night Market
address: Jl. Diponegoro, Keprabon, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57131, Indonesia

detail_description: Mrs. Lidia’s Serabi Notosuman is a must-visit in Solo, Indonesia. This local gem offers delicious Indonesian pancakes made from rice flour and coconut milk or shredded coconut. The serabi comes in two flavors: plain coconut and sweet, served with thick golden-brownish-colored coconut. While there's no seating area, visitors can request to eat on-site and enjoy the hot, crispy dough with oozing coconut milk mixture.
name: Mrs. Lidia’s Serabi Notosuman
address: Jl. Moh. Yamin No.28, Jayengan, Serengan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57152, Indonesia

excerpt: Rustic remains of a 1700s Dutch colonial fort, now used occasionally for concerts & festivals.
name: Fort Vastenburg
address: Kedung Lumbu, Pasar Kliwon, Surakarta City, Central Java 57133, Indonesia

name: Kampung Batik Kauman
address: Jl. Trisula III No.1, Kauman, Kec. Ps. Kliwon, Kota Surakarta, Jawa Tengah 57112, Indonesia

name: Kampung Batik Laweyan
address: Jl. Sidoluhur No.6, Bumi, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57148, Indonesia

detail_description: Surakarta Royal Palace, also known as Keraton Surakarta, served as the residence of the Java king who governed Central Java centuries ago. It was established in 1744 by Susuhunan Pakubuwono II after the previous palace was destroyed. The vast palace complex covers 54 acres of land and is filled with numerous rooms that hold a wealth of historical tales.
name: Surakarta Royal Palace
address: CRMX+J5J, Jagalan, Kec. Jebres, Kota Surakarta, Jawa Tengah 57162, Indonesia

excerpt: Historic area featuring shops producing batik, classically colored textiles with designs.
detail_description: Kampoeng Batik Laweyan is a historic area known for its shops producing batik, which are classically colored textiles with unique designs. In addition to exploring the food scene, visitors can also check out Pasar Antik Triwindu for antique items and Omah Sinten Heritage & Resto for a royal family treatment dinner.
name: Forum Kampoeng Batik Laweyan
address: Jl. Dr. Rajiman No.521, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57148, Indonesia

excerpt: 600-year-old temple complex dedicated to birth & new life, consisting of a pyramid & statues.
detail_description: Sukuh Temple, a 600-year-old complex located 900m above the Solo plain, offers stunning views of Gunung Lawu. The temple is known for its enigmatic and striking architecture, featuring a truncated pyramid and fascinating reliefs with Barong statues adorning the facade. It is believed to have been a site for practicing a fertility cult, earning it the nickname "the erotic temple.
name: Sukuh Temple
address: 94FJ+3J7, Tambak, Berjo, Ngargoyoso, Karanganyar Regency, Central Java 57793, Indonesia

excerpt: Royal residence since 1757, part of which is open to the public for touring historic displays.
detail_description: Mangkunegaran Palace, a royal abode since 1757, is partly open to the public for displaying historical artifacts. Unlike other fortresses surrounded by thick walls, this palace stands out with its visible location. A fee of 20k rupiahs per person is charged for entering both the museum and the palace, which is administered as Kadipaten instead of Kasultanan/Kasunanan making it comparatively smaller than Yogyakarta Palace.
name: Pura Mangkunagaran
address: Jl. Ronggowarsito, Keprabon, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57131, Indonesia

detail_description: Balekambang Park, also known as Taman Balekambang, is a picturesque public park in Solo city that offers a refreshing escape with its lush greenery. It's a popular spot for pre-wedding photoshoots and features an open amphitheater for events and plays. Visitors can interact with various animals like deer, turkey, swans, and monkeys while enjoying the playgrounds scattered throughout the park.
name: Balekambang Park
address: Jl. Balekambang, Manahan, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57139, Indonesia

excerpt: This kid-friendly recreation park has swimming pools, slides & playgrounds, plus artificial waves.
name: Pandawa Water World
address: 9RV3+RH5, Komplek Pandawa Jl. Cemara Raya Gedangan, Dusun 2, Kec. Grogol, Kabupaten Sukoharjo, Jawa Tengah 57552, Indonesia

excerpt: Marble tombs of President Soeharto & family, set in a simple, Javanese-style pavilion on a hilltop.
detail_description: Astana Giribangun is a Javanese-style pavilion located on a hilltop, housing the marble tombs of former Indonesian President Soeharto and his family. It is situated within the Mangkunegaran Royal Cemetery complex, showcasing exquisite Javanese architecture and offering breathtaking views. Mr. Soeharto was laid to rest here alongside his late wife, Mrs. Tien Soeharto. Visitors are not charged an admission fee but can donate according to their own discretion.
name: Astana Giribangun
address: Jl. Astana Giribangun, Dengkeng, Girilayu, Matesih, Karanganyar Regency, Central Java 57781, Indonesia

excerpt: Popular, old-school shopping center with 7 floors of stores plus a food court & movie theater.
detail_description: Timezone Grand Mall Solo is a renowned and traditional shopping center that boasts an impressive seven floors of diverse stores, along with an enticing food court and a movie theater. This establishment is widely appreciated for its affordability, both in terms of shopping options and dining choices. It caters to families as well, offering numerous child-friendly attractions such as the popular kid fun stations like Timezone.
name: Timezone Grand Mall Solo - Arcade Games, Bowling, Kids Birthday Party Venue
address: Grand Mall Solo, Slamet Riyadi St Jalan No.273, Penumping, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57141, Indonesia

excerpt: Popular park featuring a variety of food stalls, carnival rides & views of a sacred buffalo herd.
detail_description: Alun Alun Kidul Surakarta is a vibrant park that serves as a delightful gathering spot for both locals and visitors. Located just a short 28-minute drive from the heart of Solo, this lively area features an array of food stalls offering delicious and affordable treats, making it perfect for food lovers. As night falls, the park transforms into a bustling night market filled with energy and excitement.
name: Alun-Alun Kidul Surakarta
address: alun alun kidul, Kec. Ps. Kliwon, Kota Surakarta, Jawa Tengah 57118, Indonesia

detail_description: The royal mosque of the principality of Mangkunegaran is a beautifully designed and modern structure, even by today's standards. Despite being built in the early 20th century, it has a timeless appearance and offers excellent air circulation and natural light. Located near Solo central City, this historical building features a tall teak wood roof that helps to regulate high temperatures during hot days.
name: Masjid Al Wustho Mangkunegaran
address: Jl. Kartini No.3, Ketelan, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57132, Indonesia

excerpt: Museum honoring the national press, with a library, exhibits & more than 1 million newspapers.
detail_description: The National Press Monument, also known as Monumen Pers Nasional, is a museum and memorial dedicated to the national press of Indonesia. It was established in 1978 after being proposed for over 20 years. Situated in Surakarta, Central Java, this complex is managed by the Ministry of Communications and Information. The site includes an old society building constructed in 1918, which served as the venue for the inaugural meeting of the Reporters Association of Indonesia (PWI).
name: Monumen Pers Nasional
address: Jl. Gajahmada No.59, Timuran, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57132, Indonesia

excerpt: Java's cultural heritage is the focus at this museum with regional art, artifacts & weaponry.
detail_description: The Museum Keris Nusantara is dedicated to preserving the cultural heritage of Java, particularly its art, artifacts and weaponry. The museum has four floors showcasing a vast collection of keris and related historical items. Visitors can enjoy various facilities such as a kids corner, library, lockers, souvenirs & gift shop and cafe. The museum offers insights into traditional weapons from Java and other cultures alike.
name: Museum Keris Nusantara
address: Jl. Bhayangkara No.2, Sriwedari, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57141, Indonesia

detail_description: Loji Gandrung, an impressive historical structure located on the bustling Slamet Riyadi main street, catches the eye with its remarkable architecture. The building is meticulously maintained and currently serves as the official residence of the Mayor. Although visitors are not allowed inside, they can freely roam around the picturesque front park to capture memorable photos. Security personnel have mentioned that there are plans to transform this building into a museum; however, no specific timeline has been disclosed yet.
name: Loji Gandrung
address: CRM5+9QV, Slamet Riyadi St, Penumping, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57141, Indonesia

excerpt: Park at an old sugar factory with a playground, climbing wall, aquarium, aviaries & a water park.
detail_description: Sondokoro Agrotourism is a spacious and historical destination that was once a sugar cane plantation. With various amenities such as a playground, climbing wall, aquarium, aviaries, and water park, it offers entertainment for children and adults alike. The entrance fee of Rp 5,000 per person is worth it to experience the steam train rides on weekends for Rp 12,000.
name: Sondokoro Agrotourism
address: CWFJ+FJM, Jl. Mangkunegara Bojonegara, Nglande Wetan, Ngijo, Tasikmadu, Karanganyar Regency, Central Java 42454, Indonesia

detail_description: Dalem Kalitan, a significant historical site in Solo, is a must-visit for those interested in history. Previously a small palace belonging to the royal family of Solo, it was later acquired by Soeharto's wife's family and transformed into their holiday residence. Although no longer part of the royal palace, Dalem Kalitan continues to uphold its traditional Javanese customs.
name: Dalem Kalitan
address: CRP5+8FP, Timuran, Penumping, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57131, Indonesia

excerpt: Family complex with play areas, picnic spots & swimming pools fed by naturally cold spring water.
name: Umbul Pengging
address: CMWG+X3P, Umbulsari, Bendan, Kec. Banyudono, Kabupaten Boyolali, Jawa Tengah 57373, Indonesia

excerpt: Striking modern art owned by the founding family of a major textile firm & displayed in a mansion.
detail_description: Tumurun Private Museum is a modern art museum that showcases a contemporary collection owned by the founding family of a major textile firm. The artwork is displayed in an opulent mansion and visitors are required to pre-register on their website before being guided through the collections by staff members. Due to the pandemic, visiting hours are limited. The museum boasts remarkable collections of both art and antiques, each with its own unique story.
name: Tumurun Private Museum
address: Jl. Kebangkitan Nasional No.2, RW.4, Sriwedari, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57141, Indonesia

detail_description: The Masjid Laweyan, one of the oldest mosques in Surakarta and Central Java, was constructed in the early 20th century. Situated adjacent to the historic Laweyan cemetery, where the ancestors of Mataram kings rest, this modest yet comfortable mosque offers respite from Solo's scorching hot weather with its air-conditioned interior.
name: Masjid Laweyan
address: Jl. Liris No.1, Belukan, Pajang, Laweyan, Surakarta City, Central Java 57146, Indonesia

detail_description: Stadion Manahan in Surakarta is an ideal destination for bodyshaping activities such as jogging, various ball sports, rollerblading, and zumba. It provides a safe environment for children and offers tranquility with its abundance of big trees. Additionally, the surrounding area boasts a wide selection of affordable and delicious street foods to satisfy one's post-workout cravings. This venue also hosts music performances, with an upcoming event scheduled for August 10, 2022.
name: Stadion Manahan
address: Jl. Adi Sucipto, Manahan, Banjarsari, Surakarta City, Central Java 57139, Indonesia

excerpt: Traditional zoo with birds, mammals, elephant & camel rides & many educational programs.
detail_description: The Solo Safari zoo offers a variety of animals including elephants, tigers, eagles, crocodiles and more. There are also educational programs available for visitors to learn about the different species. The zoo has a large area for walking and an internal bus service at a reasonable price. Food options are available along the sidewalk and there is even a small playground for children. However, the zoo requires further development and attention from local government to strengthen its facilities with better renovations and more animal variants.
name: Solo Safari
address: Jl. Ir. Sutami No.109, Jebres, Surakarta City, Central Java 57126, Indonesia
